<h2>Why Profile Creation Sites Still Matter for SEO</h2>
<p>Google confirmed in 2024 that backlinks remain one of its core ranking signals. But backlinks from profiles serve a dual purpose in 2026.</p>
<p>First, they build link diversity. A <a href="https://martech.org/natural-backlink-profile/">healthy backlink profile</a> has links from many source types. Editorial links, directory links, social links, and profile links. A mix of dofollow and nofollow signals tells Google your link profile is natural.</p>
<p>Second, profile backlinks strengthen your brand entity. When Google sees your business name, website, and details on LinkedIn, Crunchbase, GitHub, and 50 other platforms, it confirms you are a real entity. Brand mentions correlate 3 times more strongly with AI search visibility than backlinks alone.</p>
<p>That does not mean you should create 500 empty profiles. Quality matters more than quantity. Fifty complete profiles with unique bios, photos, and links beat 500 blank sign-ups every time.</p>
<p>The sites below are organized by category. Each entry includes the domain authority score, link type, and a note on what makes the site useful.</p>
<h2>How to Use This List</h2>
<p>Before you start creating profiles, follow this process:</p>
<ol>
<li>Pick 5 to 10 sites per week from different categories</li>
<li>Fill out every available field on each profile</li>
<li>Write a unique 40 to 60 word bio for each platform</li>
<li>Add your website URL in the designated field</li>
<li>Upload a professional photo or branded logo</li>
<li>Use <a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">consistent NAP data</a> across every profile</li>
</ol>
<p>Creating profiles in batches of 5 to 10 per week looks natural to search engines. Mass-creating 100 profiles in a single day can trigger spam filters.</p>
